THE BREACH SKILL

Format: BREACH

Known more for their courage than their brains, some barbarians have
been known to dive head first into the enemy, tossing all allies out of
harm's way.

While foolhardy, it could be the thing that saves the day.

You can back off the breach by using the 'settle down' command.

Details:
- Utility skill which causes the user to automatically attempt to
  rescue group mates.

606H 126V 3205103X 46.07% 4878C [Dolm the fearsome blue dragon:Fair] [a mystical dragonhorse:Perfect] T:45 Exits:NESWD> 

Format: GROUP 

        GROUP form
        GROUP disband
        GROUP
        GROUP name 

Group allows leaders and their followers to organize their alliance.  Group
members work together towards a common goal.  Members will share experience
throughout combat based upon their involvement in the battle.  The final
experience split (given upon the death of the opponent) is awarded on a
share per level basis and does not depend on involvement in combat. No
final xp is awarded to sleeping members or members who are not present
during the killing blow.

Arctic was designed to strongly encourage grouping. Many things are
too hard to do solo.

Groups are structured much the same way followers are. They may be a "tree"
of group members. In any group, every group member follows another group
member. There is one leader for every group. There is a current max of 8 to
a group. Players are required to use no more than 8 characters at any given
time for a fight, or even in the zone| having more than 8 is considered an
abuse of game mechanics (see HELP POLICY).

Format: group 

      This command allows you to add to your group certain players that are
      following you. If they are already grouped then it will remove them
      from the group.

Format: group form

      This command adds to the group all those players that are currently
      following you.  It also adds any players that may be following one
      of your followers (sound confusing? It isn't| try it out and see.)
      If you are currently a member of a group, you and all followers
      are removed from that group (in order to form the new group).

Format: group disband

      This command is by far the easiest way to stop leading a group.  All
      members of the group stop following you and are free to go their own
      directions.

Format: group name 

Group names can be issued by specifying an argument to the "group name"
usage of group.  If no argument is supplied, the group name is removed.
The group name will show up in the who list for all to see.  Please use
discretion in choosing a not-so-offensive group name (such things will
be policed if necessary).

Format: group
        group full
Group with no argument shows the list of people with whom you are grouped,
together with their current hit point status, movement point status,
position, flying status, invisibility, waterbreath status and hours remaining
to memorize. It will also display your group name if there is one.  Names
preceded with an asterix (*) mean that the group member is linkdead.  Group
full will also include the pets of your group members in the list.

See also: EXPERIENCE, FOLLOW, GTELL, ASSIST, SWAP, SPLIT,
          "GROUP DETAILED", "SWAP DETAILED"

We reserve the right to delete or force a player to change his name if we feel
that it is inappropriate. Character names should be chosen in light of the world
in which Dragonlance stories take place. Compound nouns (such as Darkshadow or
Flamesword), anachronistic character names (such as Superman or Judgedredd), and
silly names (such as Mrboffo and Iamanewbie)are inappropriate. Characters with
such names will very likely be deleted. In the event you are asked to change
names (gods are not required to ask), please remember to be polite and
courteous: Staff members are here to help maintain a pleasant gaming
environment, not make your personal experience difficult.

Type 'start' to create a new character.

What is your character's name? 


start



We reserve the right to delete or force a player to change his name if we feel
that it is inappropriate. Character names should be chosen in light of the world
in which Dragonlance stories take place. Compound nouns (such as Darkshadow or
Flamesword), anachronistic character names (such as Superman or Judgedredd), and
silly names (such as Mrboffo and Iamanewbie)are inappropriate. Characters with
such names will very likely be deleted. In the event you are asked to change
names (gods are not required to ask), please remember to be polite and
courteous: Staff members are here to help maintain a pleasant gaming
environment, not make your personal experience difficult.

help guild cleric


A cleric is a generic priest, who tends to the needs of a community.  They can

serve as both protector and healer using the spells bestowed upon them by
their deity.  Clerics are granted incredible powers over undead.

Clerics are valuable to a group not only for their healing arts but also as a
moderate fighter.  Although they are not trained in martial skills they are
sturdy folk and should not be underestimated.  Because clerics are reluctant
to shed blood, they may only use blunt or bludgeoning weapons.

The clerics primary abilities are wisdom and intelligence.

Early Skills:
bludgeons               miscellaneous           turn

NOTE: Later skills must be learned about through playing the class.

Allowable Races:
all

Alignment Restrictions:
none



 [return for more, q to stop]


See also: SPELLS, GUILDS, SKILLS, RACES, EXOTIC RACES

    We require characters to be registered to an active e-mail account. We
    will not sell this information, or share it with others. This will allow
    us to help you if there is ever a problem with your character.
    Do not use a free email site.  These are unacceptable due to abuse.
    (Characters without valid email addresses may be deleted.)

                  -- ArcticMUD General Information --


These are pieces of information that we suggest you research before you
begin game play.  You can read this page at the game prompt by typing 'info'.

1.  All the basic information we think you need to play the game is 
    available through the HELP command. Type HELP by itself to see a list
    of topics which can then be read with the HELP command.

2.  You must read the disclaimer by typing HELP DISCLAIMER. You should
    also read the rules by typing HELP RULES.
    ***WARNING:  IGNORANCE IS NO DEFENSE ***

3.  New players should read HELP NEWBIE. Then read all the topics it points
    you to. Even old players can probably learn a few things here.

The roads are long and tiring, be prepared.  The game is designed for
experienced MUD players| it is full of subtle dangers, so keep your
eyes open.  Inexperienced players are welcomed to try to conquer the
game -- we have done our best to accommodate you as well.

"Life is dangerous, Caramon. Just stepping out that door is dangerous! You

 [return for more, q to stop]

cannot hide from danger. Death floats on the air, creeps through the

window, comes with the handshake of a stranger. If we stop living because
we fear death, then we have already died."
-Raistlin Majere "The Soulforge"

Enjoy your stay at Arctic.

ALSO SEE HELP ON: DISCLAIMER, RULES, NEWBIE, FAQ

eyes open.

     life.  I bind your soul to the mortal realm so you may
     play your part in the continual struggle.  This is not
     a gift.  As you will see, it can be your curse.'

Welcome to Arctic.

Arctic is a heavily modified DIKU with the experienced player in mind.
Our administration policy is not to interfere with mortal affairs.
Please bear that in mind when asking immortals for assistance.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arctic allows for each player to have two characters online at any time.
Each character must have the same email address and hostname. Any attempts
to circumvent this rule will be dealt with harshly.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Welcome to the land of Krynn.

Nowhere
    You stand in the void between the heavens above and the green sphere of
Krynn below. From here, you can see three pillars reaching up from the
depths below, holding up the universe. These three pillars are colored
black, red and white and form a triangle. As you peer closer, you notice a
fourth, almost invisible pillar in the middle of them, separate, yet still
a part of the whole. A multitude of silvery strings range out from here,
heading earthward towards various points upon Krynn. Several of the thicker
strings are so close at hand that you feel a simple thought would be
required to make contact with them.

You may choose your starting point by simply typing it or speaking the
location's name.

New players should start in:
                    SOLACE

More experienced players may elect to start in:
TARSIS    BALIFOR    KALAMAN    HAVEN    PALANTHAS    NERAKA

A bulletin board hangs motionlessly in the void around you.

haven


Your body tingles as the string touches you and then you suddenly feel

a rush of wind as you are transported!

Falling From the Heavens
     Air whips past your face as you fall towards your intended location
to begin a new life of adventure within the lands of Ansalon.  You have
no time to view the landscape as more than a blurred blob before you find
yourself at your new destination.
The Seeker's Inn
    A fire blazes in a large stone fireplace in the northern corner of
the room. Several tables are scattered around, and several occupants of
the inn are seated at the tables, ordering food and drink from the roving
waitresses. A bard sits by the fireplace, a lute slung over one shoulder.
The innkeeper smiles as you enter, and motions you to come closer so as
to hear above the loud merrymaking of the inn.
A pile of worn maps sits in the corner, free to adventurers.
A large bulletin board is mounted on a wall here.
A man in dirty green and brown garb studies the customers intently.
An old man sits by the fireplace, a lute slung over one shoulder.
The innkeeper is standing here, awaiting your request.

The Seeker's Inn

    A fire blazes in a large stone fireplace in the northern corner of
the room. Several tables are scattered around, and several occupants of
the inn are seated at the tables, ordering food and drink from the roving
waitresses. A bard sits by the fireplace, a lute slung over one shoulder.
The innkeeper smiles as you enter, and motions you to come closer so as
to hear above the loud merrymaking of the inn.
A pile of worn maps sits in the corner, free to adventurers.
A large bulletin board is mounted on a wall here.
You see the outline of a life form here, carrying: a cloak of minor distortion| a crimson cloak inlaid with threads of marble| a crimson shawl inlaid with threads of marble| a glowing scroll of recall.
A man in dirty green and brown garb studies the customers intently.
An old man sits by the fireplace, a lute slung over one shoulder.
The innkeeper is standing here, awaiting your request.

n


Northern Gate of Haven

    The northern city gates stand here, guarded by several tough looking
men.  The gates are made of steel-reinforced wooden planks, and they can
be barred from the inside to prevent the periodic goblin raiders from
gaining entrance into the town.  Far to your south stands the central
square of Haven, and beyond that, the large Temple of the New Gods.  To
your east and west a narrow lane  runs along the outside walls of the
city.
An elite guard of the city stands here, watching you closely.
An elite guard of the city stands here, watching you closely.

n


Shaman's Sanctuary

    This large tent seems to have only just been erected here, though
already it is filled with various decorations and totems. Hanging from the
cloth walls of the tent are various charms and bones of dead animals that
clatter together producing an almost musical tone. A small firepit lies in
the center of the room, from which a steady stream of thick smoke rises.
The smoke seems to dance and shift at the whim of the tribal human that
shifts about here, before making its escape through an opening in the top
of the tent.
Sekhu the guildmaster guides students on their spiritual journey.

he spe aid


Spell    : Aid

Sphere   : Protection
Usage    : cast 'aid' [person in room]
Duration : Level Based
Effect   : Gives target a temporary boost in energy and health

By means of this spell, the cleric calls upon his/her deity to help
aid the target in the coming combats in the form of a slight increase
in their hitpoints.  The target must already be at full health for
the spell to take effect.

he spe bless


Spell    : Bless

Sphere   : Combat
Usage    : cast 'bless' [char/object in room]
Duration : 5+(level/3) hours on char / permanent on objects
Effects  : Improves chance to hit and resistance to spells

This holy spell can be used on either characters or objects.
Blessing a character will improve the victim's chance to hit and magic
resistance, temporarily.

Blessing an object has permanent effects -- the item will be immune to rot
and curse spells, as well as improving its resistance to most magic. Bless
can only be used on items within a certain weight range dependent on level, in
general this applies to very large items only.  Evil objects cannot be
blessed.

Details:
- A defensive & utility spell which either adds BLESS to items or provides
  living targets with bonus HITROLL and SAVING_SPELL.
- May be recast on a target before expiration to extend duration.

What is your character's name?

We reserve the right to delete or force a player to change his name if we feel
that it is inappropriate. Character names should be chosen in light of the world
in which Dragonlance stories take place. Compound nouns (such as Darkshadow or
Flamesword), anachronistic character names (such as Superman or Judgedredd), and
silly names (such as Mrboffo and Iamanewbie)are inappropriate. Characters with
such names will very likely be deleted. In the event you are asked to change
names (gods are not required to ask), please remember to be polite and
courteous: Staff members are here to help maintain a pleasant gaming
environment, not make your personal experience difficult.

                  -- ArcticMUD General Information --


These are pieces of information that we suggest you research before you
begin game play.  You can read this page at the game prompt by typing 'info'.

1.  All the basic information we think you need to play the game is 
    available through the HELP command. Type HELP by itself to see a list
    of topics which can then be read with the HELP command.

2.  You must read the disclaimer by typing HELP DISCLAIMER. You should
    also read the rules by typing HELP RULES.
    ***WARNING:  IGNORANCE IS NO DEFENSE ***

3.  New players should read HELP NEWBIE. Then read all the topics it points
    you to. Even old players can probably learn a few things here.

The roads are long and tiring, be prepared.  The game is designed for
experienced MUD players| it is full of subtle dangers, so keep your
eyes open.  Inexperienced players are welcomed to try to conquer the
game -- we have done our best to accommodate you as well.

"Life is dangerous, Caramon. Just stepping out that door is dangerous! You

 [return for more, q to stop]

cannot hide from danger. Death floats on the air, creeps through the

window, comes with the handshake of a stranger. If we stop living because
we fear death, then we have already died."
-Raistlin Majere "The Soulforge"

Enjoy your stay at Arctic.

ALSO SEE HELP ON: DISCLAIMER, RULES, NEWBIE, FAQ

Welcome to Arctic.

Arctic is a heavily modified DIKU with the experienced player in mind.
Our administration policy is not to interfere with mortal affairs.
Please bear that in mind when asking immortals for assistance.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arctic allows for each player to have two characters online at any time.
Each character must have the same email address and hostname. Any attempts
to circumvent this rule will be dealt with harshly.

Welcome to the land of Krynn.

Nowhere
    You stand in the void between the heavens above and the green sphere of
Krynn below. From here, you can see three pillars reaching up from the
depths below, holding up the universe. These three pillars are colored
black, red and white and form a triangle. As you peer closer, you notice a
fourth, almost invisible pillar in the middle of them, separate, yet still
a part of the whole. A multitude of silvery strings range out from here,
heading earthward towards various points upon Krynn. Several of the thicker
strings are so close at hand that you feel a simple thought would be
required to make contact with them.

You may choose your starting point by simply typing it or speaking the
location's name.

Falling From the Heavens
     Air whips past your face as you fall towards your intended location
to begin a new life of adventure within the lands of Ansalon.  You have
no time to view the landscape as more than a blurred blob before you find
yourself at your new destination.
The Seeker's Inn
    A fire blazes in a large stone fireplace in the northern corner of
the room. Several tables are scattered around, and several occupants of
the inn are seated at the tables, ordering food and drink from the roving
waitresses. A bard sits by the fireplace, a lute slung over one shoulder.
The innkeeper smiles as you enter, and motions you to come closer so as
to hear above the loud merrymaking of the inn.

Welcome to Arctic.

Arctic is a heavily modified DIKU with the experienced player in mind.
Our administration policy is not to interfere with mortal affairs.
Please bear that in mind when asking immortals for assistance.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arctic allows for each player to have two characters online at any time.
Each character must have the same email address and hostname. Any attempts
to circumvent this rule will be dealt with harshly.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

he spe curse


Spell    : Curse

Sphere   : Enchantment
Usage    : cast 'curse' [opponent/object in room]
Duration : 1 day on people / permanent on objects
Effects  : Reduces chance to hit and worsens armor class

When cast on a character, the curse gives the victim terrible luck.
As a result, they are easier to hit and have more trouble hitting
their opponents. If cast on an object, the effect is permanent, and that
item can neither be dropped, nor blessed. If the object is a weapon, its
damage will be reduced.

Details:
- Utility spell which reduces victim's HITROLL and ARMOR.
- Permanent on objects, and adds CURSED and EVIL flags.
- When cast on weapons, an attack die is lost.

he spe bli


Spell    : Blindness

Sphere   : Enchantment
Usage    : cast 'blindness' [opponent]
Duration : 1+(level/6) hours/combat rounds
Effects  : Victim becomes temporarily blind

Failing a saving throw, the victim will become temporarily blind.  This will
have the effect of rendering the victim in a state of hopelessness, until the
spell wears off or is dispelled.  While blind, the victim suffers a large
penalty to their chance to hit, as well as making themselves much easier to
hit.

Movement is possible, but as you cannot see where you are going this is
often a drastic measure -- be sure that you won't be taken to an even worse
situation!

The effect duration is in hours, unless the victim is in combat, in which
case the duration is three times as long in combat rounds.  For example,
at level 3, the duration is 2 hours or 6 combat rounds.

Details:
- See above.

Spell    : Divine Intervention

Sphere   : Combat
Usage    : cast 'divine intervention' (aura)
Duration : varies
Effects  : Calls for divine intervention.

The pinnacle of the powers granted by the Gods of Good to their most devout
followers, this spell asks a deity to intefer and protect the caster's party 
from harm. Casting this spell exerts a heavy toll, bringing the caster to
the death's door, and preventing the casting of other divine powers a lot
longer than usual.

Details:
- Defensive spell which cures all non-evil group members of the caster.
- Also creates an aura that grants non-evil group members a bonus to
  LIMIT_DAMAGE_FACTOR and causes automatic success when rolling saving
  throws for a short time.

THE DIVINITY SKILL

  Format: divinity

The gods of divine power shine down upon the cleric, providing bonus
memorization speed and concentration for the duration. Other affects, such
as the ability to detect the purity of souls, may appear at higher skill
level. The power of divinity is known to help smite down enemies, adding
bonus damage to offensive spells for the duration. However, after several
offensive damage spells are cast, the divine link to the Gods will be
severed.

Details:
- Utility skill which provide a number of benefits to the caster,
  including a bonus to CONCENTRATION_FACTOR and single target spell damage.
- At higher skill levels may grant DETECT_GOOD and DETECT_EVIL, the
  benefits of MENTAL_ACUITY, a bonus to SPELL_SAVES_MOD, and DETECT_UNDEAD.

349H 132V 13090108X 1.43% 774C Mem:2 T:25 Exits:W> 

he guild scout


Scouts are masters of the wilderness and they posses a deep connection to the

land, from the animals that inhabit Krynn to the lush vegetation. Their
inherent understanding of nature provides them with many advantages
available only to them. In Krynn scouts are master hunters/trackers and
possess a greater awareness of their surroundings, especially when
outdoors.

While scouts do not possess "conventional" magic, they are highly attuned to
the creatures of Krynn and can connect on a deep level with various animals in
the land (HELP SKILL INSTINCT). This connection can provide a scout with new
abilities as well as other benefits, as long as the connection is maintained.

Scouts are highly proficient with a bow, only scouts possess the knowledge
and skill required to effectively use a bow (HELP ARCHERY). While scouts
possess a unique knowledge of ranged attacks, they also possess skills
which make them formidable in melee combat, an expert scout can prove to be
a dangerous threat from near or far.

Scouts rely on their dexterity, intelligence and strength for survival.

Early Skills:
axes                    bandage                 bludgeons
hide                    long blades             miscellaneous
piercers                shoot                   short blades


NOTE: Later skills must be learned about through playing the class.

Allowable Races:
human           qualinesti elf  silvanesti elf  kagonesti elf   half-elf
minotaur        kender          goblin          daergar dwarf   half ogre
dargonesti elf  irda

Alignment Restrictions:
none

See also: GUILDS, SKILLS, RACES, EXOTIC RACES, SKILL INSTINCT, ARCHERY
